National Transportation Safety Board
Aviation Accident Final Report
Location: ANGLETON, TX
Accident Number: FTW82DA205
Date & Time: 06/01/1982, 0600 CDT
Registration: N8974H
Aircraft: GRUMMAN G-164A
Aircraft Damage: Destroyed
Defining Event:
Injuries: 1 None
Flight Conducted Under: Part 137: Agricultural
 Analysis WHILE CONCENTRATING ON HIS FLAGGER, THE PILOT MISJUDGED HIS ALTITUDE AND ALLOWED THE AIRCRAFT TO COLLIDE WITH A LEVEE.
THE PILOT THEN DUMPED HIS LOAD AND MADE AN EMERGENCY LANDING, DURING WHICH TIME, THE AIRCRAFT NOSED OVER.
Probable Cause and Findings The National Transportation Safety Board determines the probable cause(s) of this accident to be: Findings Occurrence #1: IN FLIGHT COLLISION WITH TERRAIN/WATER Phase of Operation: MANEUVERING - AERIAL APPLICATION Findings 1.
(F) TERRAIN CONDITION - DIRT BANK/RISING EMBANKMENT 2.
(C) ALTITUDE - MISJUDGED - PILOT IN COMMAND 3.
DIVERTED ATTENTION - PILOT IN COMMAND 4.
